      ";s:2:"dc";a:2:{s:7:"creator";s:25:"David Smith in Washington";s:4:"date";s:20:"2020-04-30T10:15:18Z";}s:7:"summary";s:622:"<p>The taskforce coordinator has tried to walk a diplomatic tightrope – but has failed to speak out against the president’s false claims</p><p>Sometimes the story is not so much Donald Trump as the people around him, and not so much what they say but what they don’t.</p><p> <span>Related: </span><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/apr/29/trump-coronavirus-america-richard-wolffe">Trump the commander-in-bleach has been stripped of all feeling | Richard Wolffe</a> </p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/apr/30/dr-deborah-birx-coronavirus-taskforce-trump">Continue reading...</a>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1588241718;}i:5;a:11:{s:5:"title";s:67:"Promising drug against Covid-19 unlikely to be available in UK soon";s:4:"link";s:115:"https://www.theguardian.com/science/2020/apr/30/promising-drug-against-covid-19-unlikely-to-be-available-in-uk-soon";s:11:"description";s:866:"<p>Trial of remdesivir shows fewer deaths and shorter hospital stays</p><ul><li><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/series/coronavirus-live/latest">Coronavirus – latest updates</a></li><li><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/coronavirus-outbreak">See all our coronavirus coverage</a></li></ul><p>The first drug against Covid-19 to show promise in trials, reducing the time seriously ill people take to recover in hospital, is unlikely to be available widely in the UK soon, it has emerged.</p><p>Forty-six people in the UK have received remdesivir as part of the European arm of an international trial. Researchers would like to have given the drug to more patients but did not have the supplies.</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2020/apr/30/promising-drug-against-covid-19-unlikely-to-be-available-in-uk-soon">Continue reading...</a>";s:8:"category";s:87:"Medical researchHealthPharmaceuticals industryCoronavirus outbreakScien