tensive investigations into its star painting, <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2002/nov/02/art">Johannes Vermeer’s Girl with a Pearl Earring</a>, thought to date from about 1665. </p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2020/apr/28/dutch-researchers-coax-secrets-from-girl-with-a-pearl-earring">Continue reading...</a>";s:8:"category";s:113:"Johannes VermeerArt and designMuseumsPaintingNetherlandsCultureEuropeWorld newsResearch and developmentTechnology";s:7:"pubdate";s:29:"Tue, 28 Apr 2020 13:33:49 GMT";s:4:"guid";s:114:"https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2020/apr/28/dutch-researchers-coax-secrets-from-girl-with-a-pearl-earring";s:5:"media";a:2:{s:7:"content";s:18:"
        
