      ";s:2:"dc";a:2:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"Vic Marks";s:4:"date";s:20:"2020-04-30T18:00:02Z";}s:7:"summary";s:840:"<p>When the short form was conceived in 2002 the cricket calendar was not so crowded and the format was one club players had been enjoying for years</p><p>A common refrain to those of us who are not hanging out the bunting at the news the Hundred will be on our screens and in our Test grounds in 2021 is that all the curmudgeons were just as negative about the advent of Twenty20 cricket in 2003.</p><p>This is an easy parallel to draw and a simplistic one. Let me try to correct it. The proposal to introduce T20 cricket 18 years ago was truly radical; the ECB was introducing a new format for professional cricketers (though club players had been enjoying a similar version for years).</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2020/apr/30/twenty20-success-no-guarantee-hundred-will-produce-the-numbers">Continue reading...</a>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1588269602;}i:51;a:11:{s:5:"title";s:69:"Fifa takes action after Swiss drop part of Sepp Blatter investigation";s:4:"link";s:109:"https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/apr/30/fifa-action-after-swiss-drop-part-sepp-blatter-investigation";s:11:"description";s:949:"<ul><li>Swiss attorney general at odds with Fifa</li><li>Police reports allege gifts made in return for votes</li></ul><p>Fifa is preparing to press the authorities in Switzerland to prosecute Sepp Blatter for alleged corruption, after the Swiss attorney general dropped part of its investigation despite police reports listing years of apparent gifts and payments provided to the then <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/sep/29/jack-warner-banned-football-life-fifa-ethics-committee">vice-president, Jack Warner</a>, in return for votes for Blatter in Fifa presidential elections. </p><p>Senior Fifa officials are understood to be considering all options if the case against Blatter is discontinued, potentially including suing the attorney general’s office for failing to prosecute.</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/apr/30/fifa-action-after-swiss-drop-part-sepp-blatter-investigation">Continue reading...</a>";s:8:"category";s:57:"FootballFifaSepp BlatterJack WarnerFootball politicsSport";s:7:"pubdate";s:29:"Thu, 30 Apr 2020 16:25:50 GMT";s:4:"guid";s:109:"https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/apr/30/fifa-action-after-swiss-drop-part-sepp-blatter-investigation";s:5:"media";a:2:{s:7:"content";s:18:"
        
