      ";s:2:"dc";a:2:{s:7:"creator";s:16:"Associated Press";s:4:"date";s:20:"2020-04-30T13:03:19Z";}s:7:"summary";s:856:"<p>Investigators found Brooklyn facility had rented four trucks to hold about 50 corpses on ice, as funeral homes struggle in state amid coronavirus</p><p>Police were called to a Brooklyn neighborhood on Wednesday after a funeral home overwhelmed by the coronavirus resorted to storing dozens of bodies on ice in rented trucks, and a passerby complained about the smell, officials said.</p><p>Investigators who responded to a 911 call found that the home had rented four trucks to hold about 50 corpses, according to a law enforcement official. No criminal charges were brought and the official, who was not authorized to speak publicly about the investigation, spoke to the Associated Press on condition of anonymity.</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/30/new-york-police-funeral-home-stored-bodies-ice-trucks">Continue reading...</a>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1588251799;}i:62;a:11:{s:5:"title";s:70:"France to sell some of nation's antique furniture to support hospitals";s:4:"link";s:115:"https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/30/france-to-sell-some-of-nations-antique-furniture-to-support-hospitals";s:11:"description";s:810:"<p>About 100 objects dating from 19th century expected to be auctioned by Mobilier National </p><ul><li><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/series/coronavirus-live/latest">Coronavirus – latest updates</a></li><li><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/coronavirus-outbreak">See all our coronavirus coverage</a></li></ul><p>France is to sell off some of the nation’s antique furniture to support the country’s hard-pressed hospitals.</p><p>The <a href="http://www.mobiliernational.culture.gouv.fr/">Mobilier National</a>, the national furniture collection, is drawing up a list of objects in storage that will be auctioned off in September.</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/30/france-to-sel