agines patriotic nostalgia taken to extremes. It’s 10 years after a revolution in which Queen Bear seized power, claiming to carry the spirit of King Arthur. Britain is now on the brink of civil war, as Queen Bear’s authority is challenged by the followers of Galahad. Stuck in the middle of these two factions, protagonist Avalon is struggling with what to believe.</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2020/apr/30/the-good-book-review-intrigue-unease-dystopia">Continue reading...</a>";s:8:"category";s:23:"StageTheatreCultureFilm";s:7:"pubdate";s:29:"Thu, 30 Apr 2020 17:00:00 GMT";s:4:"guid";s:91:"https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2020/apr/30/the-good-book-review-intrigue-unease-dystopia";s:5:"media";a:2:{s:7:"content";s:18:"
        
