a small patty of minced beef grey. I mean a multi-sensory, artery-clogging, warm hug of an experience – like the sorcerers in our favourite burger places used to do on a daily basis before lockdown abruptly closed them.</p><p>Given that we could do with a bit of comfort eating right now, I decided to get some of these sorcerers on the phone to see if they could help us recreate their magic in our own kitchens. So let’s start with the most important ingredient … no, not the meat!</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2020/apr/29/the-pickle-goes-under-the-patty-how-to-make-the-perfect-burger-at-home">Continue reading...</a>";s:8:"category";s:34:"BurgersFoodMeatBreadLife and style";s:7:"pubdate";s:29:"Wed, 29 Apr 2020 10:30:13 GMT";s:4:"guid";s:115:"https://www.theguardian.com/food/2020/apr/29/the-pickle-goes-under-the-patty-how-to-make-the-perfect-burger-at-home";s:5:"media";a:2:{s:7:"content";s:18:"
        
